main event: A bright, fast-moving object was observed in the sky over St. Augustine, Florida on May 1, 1965.
interesting points: The object was initially thought to be a satellite, but then it dimmed and seemed to disappear.
The observation lasted for about 5 minutes.
The Air Force requested that the observer, Mr. W. Hartmann, be interviewed to obtain more details about the observation.
There is a hand-drawn diagram showing the trajectory of the object's movement from northwest to southeast.
The Air Force acknowledged receipt of the report and stated that it would be included in their files.
sighted object: A bright, fast-moving object in the sky
witnesses: Mr. W. Hartmann and three other observers
